@startuml CDN_Management_System_Sequence
!theme plain
title CDN Management System - Main User Flows

actor "User" as User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Express Server" as Server
participant "Auth Middleware" as Auth
participant "WebSocket" as WS
participant "MySQL Database" as DB
participant "CDN Nodes" as CDN
participant "File System" as FS
participant "Real Data Collector" as RDC

== Authentication Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Access application
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/auth/profile
Server -> Auth: Verify JWT token
Auth -> DB: Query user data
DB -> Auth: Return user info
Auth -> Server: User authenticated
Server -> Frontend: User profile data
Frontend -> User: Show dashboard/login

alt User not authenticated
    User -> Frontend: Enter credentials
    Frontend -> Server: POST /api/auth/login
    Server -> DB: Verify credentials
    DB -> Server: User data
    Server -> Frontend: JWT token + user info
    Frontend -> User: Redirect to dashboard
end

== Real-time Dashboard Monitoring ==
Frontend -> WS: Connect WebSocket
WS -> Frontend: Connection established

loop Real-time updates
    RDC -> CDN: Collect metrics
    CDN -> RDC: Return performance data
    RDC -> DB: Store metrics
    RDC -> WS: Broadcast updates
    WS -> Frontend: Real-time metrics
    Frontend -> User: Update dashboard
end

User -> Frontend: Request dashboard data
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/metrics/dashboard
Server -> Auth: Verify permissions
Auth -> DB: Query dashboard metrics
DB -> Server: System overview data
Server -> Frontend: Dashboard data
Frontend -> User: Display dashboard

== Node Management Flow ==
User -> Frontend: View CDN nodes
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/nodes
Server -> Auth: Check permissions
Auth -> DB: Query cdn_nodes table
DB -> Server: Nodes list with status
Server -> Frontend: Nodes data
Frontend -> User: Display nodes grid

User -> Frontend: View node details
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/nodes/:id/performance
Server -> Auth: Verify access
Auth -> DB: Query node_metrics table
DB -> Server: Performance data
Server -> Frontend: Node performance
Frontend -> User: Show performance charts

User -> Frontend: Update node status
Frontend -> Server: PUT /api/nodes/:id/status
Server -> Auth: Check update permissions
Auth -> DB: Update cdn_nodes status
DB -> Server: Confirmation
Server -> WS: Broadcast status change
WS -> Frontend: Real-time update
Frontend -> User: Status updated

== Content Management Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Upload content
Frontend -> Server: POST /api/content/upload (multipart)
Server -> Auth: Verify upload permissions
Auth -> FS: Save file to storage
FS -> Server: File path
Server -> DB: Store content metadata
DB -> Server: Content ID
Server -> Frontend: Upload success
Frontend -> User: Upload completed

User -> Frontend: Distribute content
Frontend -> Server: POST /api/content/:id/distribute
Server -> Auth: Check permissions
Auth -> DB: Query content and target nodes
DB -> Server: Content and nodes data

loop For each target node
    Server -> CDN: Deploy content to node
    CDN -> Server: Deployment status
    Server -> DB: Update content_distribution
end

Server -> Frontend: Distribution status
Frontend -> User: Show distribution results

== Alert Management Flow ==
loop Continuous monitoring
    RDC -> CDN: Monitor node health
    CDN -> RDC: Health metrics
    
    alt Critical threshold exceeded
        RDC -> DB: Create alert record
        RDC -> WS: Broadcast alert
        WS -> Frontend: Real-time alert
        Frontend -> User: Show alert notification
    end
end

User -> Frontend: View alerts
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/alerts
Server -> Auth: Check permissions
Auth -> DB: Query alerts table
DB -> Server: Alerts list
Server -> Frontend: Alerts data
Frontend -> User: Display alerts

User -> Frontend: Resolve alert
Frontend -> Server: POST /api/alerts/:id/resolve
Server -> Auth: Verify permissions
Auth -> DB: Update alert status
DB -> Server: Confirmation
Server -> WS: Broadcast resolution
WS -> Frontend: Update alert status
Frontend -> User: Alert resolved

== Analytics and Reporting ==
User -> Frontend: View analytics
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/analytics/performance-trends
Server -> Auth: Check permissions
Auth -> DB: Complex analytics query
note right of DB: Joins multiple tables:\n- node_metrics\n- cdn_nodes\n- access_logs
DB -> Server: Analytics data
Server -> Frontend: Processed analytics
Frontend -> User: Display charts and reports

== User Management Flow ==
User -> Frontend: Manage users (Admin only)
Frontend -> Server: GET /api/permissions/users
Server -> Auth: Check admin permissions
Auth -> DB: Query users and roles
DB -> Server: Users data
Server -> Frontend: Users list
Frontend -> User: Display user management

User -> Frontend: Update user permissions
Frontend -> Server: PUT /api/permissions/users/:id
Server -> Auth: Verify admin access
Auth -> DB: Update user permissions
DB -> Server: Confirmation
Server -> Frontend: Update success
Frontend -> User: Permissions updated

== Access Logging ==
note over Server, DB: All API requests are logged
Server -> DB: INSERT into access_logs
note right of DB: Tracks:\n- User actions\n- API endpoints\n- Timestamps\n- IP addresses

@enduml